| **4. Log parsing** | `line.split(" ")` with index gymnastics | Three compiled `re.compile()` patterns (`_LOG_RE`, `_USER_RE`, `_API_RE`) with named groups |
| **5. Types & docs** | None | Type-annotated dataclasses (`LogEntry`, `UserEvent`, `ApiCall`, `TransformedData`), full type hints on all functions, module + function docstrings |

The `report.html` output is byte-identical to the original for the sample data, and `PIPELINE_DB_PASS` no longer leaks a default password.
